---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Words with Prefix TELE in Scrabble — Top Scoring Words & Bingo Strategy"
  description="Master TELE prefix words in Scrabble. Top plays include TELEGRAM, TELEPHONE, TELESCOPE, TELEPLAY. Strategy for using this 4-tile prefix to land high-scoring bingos."
  keywords="words with prefix tele scrabble, tele words scrabble, telegram scrabble points, tele bingo scrabble, tele prefix strategy, scrabble words starting with tele"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({ "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Article", "headline": "Words with Prefix TELE in Scrabble — Top Scoring Words & Bingo Strategy", "description": "Master TELE prefix words in Scrabble. Top plays include TELEGRAM, TELEPHONE, TELESCOPE, TELEPLAY.", "datePublished": "2026-06-23", "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" }, "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" }, "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-with-prefix-tele" } })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({ "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": [ { "@type": "Question", "name": "What are the best TELE prefix words in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Top TELE words include TELEPLAY (13pts), TELEGRAM (11pts), TELECAST (10pts), TELETYPE (13pts), and TELEVISE (11pts). TELEPLAY scores highest due to Y(4) and P(3) tiles." } }, { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can TELE help me get a bingo in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Absolutely! TELE uses 4 common tiles (T+E+L+E), leaving you just 3 tiles short of a 7-letter bingo. TELECAST and TELEMARK are achievable bingos with common remaining letters." } }, { "@type": "Question", "name": "How many points is the TELE prefix worth?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The TELE prefix costs 4 points (T=1, E=1, L=1, E=1). All low-value common tiles — meaning they're easy to collect and the real scoring comes from what you add after." } } ] })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Prefix Guides</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Words with Prefix TELE in Scrabble</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-23">June 23, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">TELE (meaning "far" or "at a distance") is a Scrabble player's dream prefix. Built entirely from common 1-point tiles, it's easy to collect on your rack and opens the door to numerous high-scoring extensions. From TELEGRAM to TELEPLAY, these words combine accessible tiles with strong scoring potential.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Prefix Tiles</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Base Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">15+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid Extensions</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Tiles to Bingo</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top TELE Words by Score</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">TELEPLAY — 13 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 letters. A play written for TV. Y(4) and P(3) push this to the top. Strong bingo at 63 total.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">TELETYPE — 13 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 letters. An electromechanical typewriter. Y(4) and P(3) add value. Bingo-worthy at 63 total.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">TELEGRAM — 11 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 letters. A wired message. G(2) and M(3) add value. Classic bingo play worth 61 with bonus.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">TELECAST — 10 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 letters. A TV broadcast. C(3) drives the score. Achievable bingo with common letters.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More TELE Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TELEVISE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TELEMARK</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TELEPORT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TELEPATH</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TELEFILM</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">TELE Bingo Strategy</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">All 1-point tiles:</span> T, E, L, E are common and cheap. You'll draw them frequently — recognize the TELE pattern on your rack when it appears.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Duplicate E advantage:</span> TELE uses two E's — the most common tile in the bag. Having two E's is usually a problem, but with TELE it becomes an asset.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Key completers:</span> After TELE, look for: CAST (C+A+S+T), GRAM (G+R+A+M), PLAY (P+L+A+Y), VISE (V+I+S+E). All use common letters.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Board reading:</span> Scan for existing T, E, or L on the board. Playing through an existing letter means you place only 3 tiles but get credit for all 4.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">TELE vs AUTO Comparison</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ TELE Advantages</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">All 1-point tiles (easy to draw). Double-E is common. Many valid completions. Works in both dictionaries.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⚡ Compared to AUTO</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">AUTO uses a U (harder to place elsewhere). TELE's double-E is more common in the bag. Both have similar bingo potential.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-with-prefix-auto/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words with Prefix AUTO: Self-Governing Scrabble Plays</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/words-with-prefix-mono/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words with Prefix MONO: Single-Meaning Power Words</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find all TELE words instantly — enter your tiles and see every valid play</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
